The staff was friendly enough and the menu looked interesting. I had been scouting for some Indian or Eastern shawarmas or something, when I saw Windy City Gyros. I decided that gyros is close enough to shawarma for a hungry me.  When I noticed the cheese fries, I became enthusiastic. I love cheese fries when the cheese was melted over the hot freshly fried fries snd slowly gets a little harder add the fries chool a little. It's especially good with the little salt and ketchup.  But when I started eating and opened up the fries, I noticed that the cheese seemed to be the synthetic cheese sauce one buys at places like Walmart. It looks a little like cheese and vaguely tastes like it. But the texture is all wrong and, really, so is the flavor.  The Gyros was ok, but nothing spectacular. I was hoping that at least the sauce would taste more like Tzatziki, but not really.  I won't stop there again.

Usually, a great place. Rating from 5 to 2. I called to place an order for pickup 4 days ago, about 35min prior to arriving there. I was told it will be ready in 10min. Cool. I just needed it to be ready so I  could simply pay, grab, and go.  Here's the issue. They had my order written down sitting on the counter, yet it wasn't even done. Literally like an after thought. Nothing on my order had been done. It wasn't until after I paid and was handed a ticket and told to wait about 1min or 2, until they called the number I was given.  Yeah, that turned into a 15min wait for hastily prepared food that wasn't up to their usual quality that I love. All of the chicken breast on pitas that I ordered were tasteless. Even the toasted pitas didn't have the typical quality. The french fries were regular old fries. Nothing special. The entire meal was blah, and ended up half eaten and tossed out. A waste of $29.33 -- very disappointing.  Windy City Gyros is my favourite place for chicken breast on pitas. Been coming here on and off since I was a small child. But this time it definitely wasn't it. I probably won't be ordering anything from here in the afternoon. I'll just stick with coming in the evening on the occassions I do stop by.
